Users have a requirement to distinguish between the author and the committer in pre-receive hooks etc. 

Although this is possible to get the committer information via the low-level git API, it's much more cumbersome than the higher-level API which returns for example {{com.atlassian.bitbucket.commit.Commit}} objects. 

Consider adding the following methods to {{Commit}}:

{code:java}
@Nonnull
Person getCommitter();

@Nonnull
Date getCommitterTimestamp();
{code}

It appears to be impossible to add a comment to the last line of a file in a pull request. Even when the last line has a change. The second-to-last line shows the "+" icon and the "Add a comment on this line." tooltip, but the last line does not.

Its not very common to want to comment on the last line, so this is a fairly minor issue. But recently I had a reason to do it, and I had to leave the comment on the second to last line instead.

