A look at the stash's profiling log of a local instance shows multiple occurrences of the following error:

{noformat}
Unmatched Timer.  Was expecting "foo" instead got "bar"
{noformat}

For example, this can be seen after a push:
{noformat}
Unmatched Timer.  Was expecting /usr/local/bin/git receive-pack /Users/pepoirot/Dev/apps-home/stash-default/data/repositories/51, instead got SSH - git-receive-pack '/project_1/linux.git'
{noformat}

This is caused by the combination of two things:

# the utilisation of a ThreadLocal in [UtilTimerStack|https://bitbucket.org/atlassian/atlassian-profiling/src/c244da31635937fbb47cef7da31cfed8760b4b2f/src/main/java/com/atlassian/util/profiling/UtilTimerStack.java?at=atlassian-profiling-1.9#cl-39] to store a snapshot of the current time / memory usage in _atlassian-profiling_:
{code:java}
UtilTimerStack.push("foo");
try {
// do stuff
} finally {
   UtilTimerStack.pop("bar");
}
{code}
 (Thus if the _push()_ and _pop()_ operations do not occur in the same thread, the snapshots don't match and the class logs the _"Unmatched Timer"_ error.)
# and the utilisation of the [ProfilingProcessMonitor|https://stash.dev.internal.atlassian.com/projects/STASH/repos/stash/browse/platform/src/main/java/com/atlassian/stash/internal/process/ProfilingProcessMonitor.java?at=refs%2Ftags%2Fstash-parent-2.10.0] in Stash, which invoke the push / pop operations in different threads:
{noformat}
### push ### ssh-scm-request-handler ### SSH - git-receive-pack '/project_1/linux.git'
...
### push ### ssh-scm-request-handler ### Ticket com.atlassian.stash.throttle.ThrottleService.acquireTicket(String)
### pop  ### ssh-scm-request-handler ### Ticket com.atlassian.stash.throttle.ThrottleService.acquireTicket(String)
### push ### ssh-scm-request-handler ### /usr/local/bin/git receive-pack /Users/pepoirot/Dev/apps-home/stash-default/data/repositories/51
### pop  ### ExtProcess - IO Pump:thread-7 ### /usr/local/bin/git receive-pack /Users/pepoirot/Dev/apps-home/stash-default/data/repositories/51
### pop  ### ssh-scm-request-handler ### SSH - git-receive-pack '/project_1/linux.git'
{noformat}

As seen above, the last _push()_ occurs in the _ssh-scm-request-handler_ while the corresponding _pop()_ occurs in one of the process's IO pump in process-utils.

After discussing with [~cofarrell], the problem seems to date back to at least Stash 2.0, when _ProfilingProcessMonitor_ was introduced to [replace the manual call in BaseCommand |https://stash.dev.internal.atlassian.com/projects/STASH/repos/stash/commits/1af15a0ca8748ba5f6aef385c886f88b4d391ff4#spi/src/main/java/com/atlassian/stash/scm/BaseCommand.java].
